    • Method Detail

      • robotInit

        public void robotInit()
        This is called when the robot is first started up. All subsystem initialization is done here, by calling their respected getInstance() methods. Also, a SendableChooser object for choosing auto modes is sent to Smart Dashboard.
        Overrides:
        robotInit in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.IterativeRobot

      • disabledInit

        public void disabledInit()
        This function is called once each time the robot enters Disabled mode. Disabled mode is when the amount of joysticks connected are insufficient for the code.
        Overrides:
        disabledInit in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.IterativeRobot

      • disabledPeriodic

        public void disabledPeriodic()
        This function is called when the robot is in Disabled mode. I don't think there's every a need to actually use this function.
        Overrides:
        disabledPeriodic in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.IterativeRobot

      • autonomousInit

        public void autonomousInit()
        This function is called when the robot first enters auto. This function finds the auto command that is selected in Smart Dashboard, and runs it.
        Overrides:
        autonomousInit in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.IterativeRobot

      • autonomousPeriodic

        public void autonomousPeriodic()
        This function is called periodically during autonomous (~20ms). This function just continues the command started in autonomousInit().
        Overrides:
        autonomousPeriodic in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.IterativeRobot

      • teleopInit

        public void teleopInit()
        This function is run when the robot first enters teleop. All this function does is end the autonomous command if it's still running. NOTE: One doesn't actually need to stop the command, it is simply done so that the drivers aren't confused and call it a software "issue".
        Overrides:
        teleopInit in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.IterativeRobot

      • teleopPeriodic

        public void teleopPeriodic()
        This function is called periodically during teleop (~20ms). This function just continues to run commands either triggered in the OI class, or the default commands for any given subsystem.
        Overrides:
        teleopPeriodic in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.IterativeRobot

      • testPeriodic

        public void testPeriodic()
        This function is called periodically during test mode (~20ms). It allows testing to be done is Smart Dashboard.
        Overrides:
        testPeriodic in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.IterativeRobot
